            "worstRating": "1"
          },
          "reviewBody": "Air Force School in Gurugram, located on Delhi road, is a highly acclaimed educational institution that has been providing quality education since its inception in 1976. The school is primarily designed to cater to the needs of the children of Air Force personnel, Defence Service personnel and Defence Civilians.\n\nWith a teacher-student ratio of 1:27 and a total of 35 teachers, out of which 29 are postgraduate teachers, the school provides an excellent academic environment. The percentage of teachers with a postgraduate degree is an impressive 82.86%, ensuring a high level of academic standards.\n\nThe school offers English and Hindi as the languages of instruction and is affiliated to CBSE, ensuring that the students receive an education that is recognised throughout India. The facilities at the school include 24 classrooms, basketball, volleyball, badminton, yoga and taekwondo, providing students with ample opportunities to develop their skills.\n\nThe girls to boy ratio is 1:1.12, with 504 boys and 450 girls, and the school ensures that the class sizes are reasonable, with a student per class ratio of 39.75. The school fee is categorised separately for officers, defence and civilian, ranging from 33k to 44k. However, transport facilities are not currently available.\n\nThe school's Class 10th results are impressive, with 15% of students scoring above 90%, a testament to the high academic standards set by the school. Although the school currently only offers classes up to Class 10, it provides a solid foundation for the students' future academic pursuits.\n\nOverall, Air Force School in Gurugram is a highly recommended school that provides a safe and enriching environment for students to learn and grow. The school's emphasis on quality education, well-qualified teachers, and a wide range of facilities make it an ideal choice for parents seeking an excellent academic institution for their children.",
